List of Pokémon by body style

From Bulbapedia, the community-driven Pokémon encyclopedia.
Jump to: navigation, search
It has been suggested that this article be moved to List of Pokémon by shape.
Please discuss whether or not to move it on its talk page.

This is a list of Pokémon by their body style according to the Pokédex. This listing is available as a search method in the Pokédex from Pokémon Diamond and Pearl to Pokémon Ultra Sun and Ultra Moon. As the games only use symbols to define each group, the titles below are simply fan-created descriptions. The concept is referred to in-game as body style (Japanese: かたち style) in Generation IV, form (Japanese: 形 form) in Generation IV and V, and as shape (Japanese: 形 shape) in Generation VI and VII.

Pokémon with multiple forms may be listed differently depending on the sprite used in the main Pokédex entry, which can be changed in Generation V and VI. Currently, the Pokémon whose forms differ drastically enough for this to apply to are Slowbro, Pinsir, Giratina, the Forces of Nature, Zygarde, Hoopa, Lycanroc, Wishiwashi, and Necrozma.

Changes

In Pokémon X and Y, the body style of 11 species of Pokémon were changed.

  • Caterpie, Weedle, and Wurmple: →
  • Burmy and Wormadam: →
  • Shellos, Gastrodon and Cresselia: →
  • Tornadus (Therian Forme): →
  • Thundurus (Therian Forme): →
  • Landorus (Therian Forme): →

In Pokémon Omega Ruby and Alpha Sapphire, the body style of one species of Pokémon was changed.

  • Mega Pinsir: →
